 is leading to; away for the principal of functionality and simplicity by which it was founded and by which it can still be justified.','theJSJ v3.0','','private','closed','closed','','thejsj-v3-0','','','2012-10-25 11:55:27','2012-10-25 11:55:27','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=77',8,'piece','',0),(78,1,'2011-08-19 19:41:12','2011-08-19 19:41:12','','Portfolio - The JSJ','','inherit','open','open','','portfolio-the-jsj','','','2011-08-19 19:41:12','2011-08-19 19:41:12','',77,'http://thejsj.com/newportfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Portfolio-The-JSJ.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(79,1,'2011-08-19 19:47:28','2011-08-19 19:47:28','Site designed for the Iberoamerican Leadership Congress 2011 held in Puerto Rico.\r\n\r\nThe site as designed mostly as a portal for information related to the congress. This is mainly a content site and was designed accordingly (through it\'s horizontallity, through it\'s white background and typography). The experience is designed for the user to read. Social Media was also integrated to promote the congress among it\'s visitros.\r\n\r\nThe design is based on the previous logo design. The pallette utilizes diffrent flavos of blue to contrast elements in the page. Also diffrent shades of gray were used and incoporated almost as a fade of the dominant blue background. This type of light gray was used mostly to differentiate diffrent spaces in the page. The menu typography is also very intresting in how it was utilized as a way to mark both, the professional aspect of the conferencas as well as the youth of it\'s participants.\r\n\r\n<em>This site will be launched very shortly and is on the final stages of it\'s design.</em>','Iberoamerican Leadership Congress.org','','private','closed','closed','','iberoamerican-leadership-congress-org-2','','','2012-10-25 11:55:27','2012-10-25 11:55:27','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=79',2,'piece','',0),(80,1,'2011-08-19 19:49:09','2011-08-19 19:49:09','This website was done for a the Chatka Summer camp.\r\n\r\nThe site is a very simple site, done over a year ago. The site is a basic presentation site for the camp. Because of this a very simple layout was used. The design was a combination of a redesign, taking some of the features used in the previous site and new ideas. The aesthethics of the site reference the camp brand and logo (dark yellos, light browns) while making use of the \'outdoors\' present in previous design and very portinent for this type of summer camp.\r\n\r\nThe site employs Jquery technology for galleries and tabs, animated GIFS for the menus, Flickr embeddeds and simple HTML.','ChatkaCamp.org','','draft','closed','closed','','chatkacamp-org','','','2012-10-25 11:55:11','2012-10-25 11:55:11','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=80',29,'piece','',0),(81,1,'2011-08-19 19:48:57','2011-08-19 19:48:57','','www.chatkacamp.org','','inherit','open','open','','www-chatkacamp-org','','','2011-08-19 19:48:57','2011-08-19 19:48:57','',80,'http://thejsj.com/newportfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/www.chatkacamp.org_.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(82,1,'2011-08-19 19:52:19','2011-08-19 19:52:19','Website done for InterLeacroft, a proyect established in 2009 to launch and promote the Romanization of Intellectual Property.\r\n\r\nFor this emerging and daring undertaking, a website was created to showcase and present the institution and it\'s ideas. As such, the sites presents what the institution does, serves as a platform for trainings and courses and for spreading the ideas of this proposition thru the intituion\'s blog.\r\n\r\nIn terms of design, the image of the instituion was considered at all times. The pallette and typography utilized, both in the website and in the logo, serve to show the balance between the innovation inspired by what the proyect proposes and the formality intertwined in the legal tradition.\r\n\r\nThe site was created utilizing Joomla CMS technology. The technical part of the proyect was an challenge considering the necesity of having a website available in both English and Spanish. Also the site is integrated to PayPal for some e-comerece features requested by the client to book Training and enable the selling of a book.','Interleacroft.com','','draft','closed','closed','','interleacroft-com','','','2012-10-25 11:55:11','2012-10-25 11:55:11','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=82',30,'piece','',0),(83,1,'2011-08-19 19:50:40','2011-08-19 19:50:40','','interleacroft','','inherit','open','open','','interleacroft','','','2011-08-19 19:50:40','2011-08-19 19:50:40','',82,'http://thejsj.com/newportfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/interleacroft.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(84,1,'2011-01-15 19:58:51','2011-01-15 19:58:51','The Modern Addendum was a site complete for rock journalist and friend Enrique Olivares. As he himself puts it: \"The Modern Addendum is an amalgamation of rock n’ roll criticism and other tidbits deign of study.\" The site touches up on rock and roll, album revies, upcoming bands, jersey shore and more!\r\n\r\nAmong some of the interesting elements behind the side, the design behind it is the first of series of experiments with the idea of random color. A lof of the elements on the site change colors based on programming scripts written to generate them. The idea of letting the computer randomly decide which colors each user will see is very intriguing. Every user sees a diffrent site, each and every time they enter. It is never static. Also the randomness behind it leads to the challenge of designing other elements that combine with each and every color of the spectrum. Some of the ideas experimented here, later went on to be used in this site also.\r\n\r\nReally, go read and see... it\'s worth it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The Modern Addendum','','publish','closed','closed','','the-modern-addendum','','','2012-10-25 11:55:11','2012-10-25 11:55:11','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=84',22,'piece','',0),(85,